solution: ```class Solution {
    public boolean isSubsequence(String s, String t) {
        int i = 0, j = 0;
        while (i < s.length() && j < t.length()) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == t.charAt(j)) i++;
            j++;
        }
        return i == s.length();
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(|t|)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Single pass through t with two pointers; minimal CPU and memory usage. For the follow-up, preprocess t into a map<char, List<Integer>> storing indices of each character, then binary-search for each s character’s next valid position in t, achieving O(|s| log |t|) per query after O(|t|) preprocessing.

